<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Cakile</i> <i>edentula</i> or <i>Cakile</i> <i>maritima</i> is dominant in the herbaceous layer. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 50 cm; cover is sparse. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Bare sand at the leading edge of the beach, within the reach of storm tides and extreme lunar tides. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Cakile edentula</i> as a FACU plant and <i>Cakile maritima</i> as a FACW plant. </div>
</div>

		
